docs.abstract: Disney’s deal for Fox’s assets faces a new challenge from Comcast. No matter which comes out on top, it is Rupert Murdoch who will be the real winner.
docs.snippet: Disney’s deal for Fox’s assets faces a new challenge from Comcast. No matter which comes out on top, it is Rupert Murdoch who will be the real winner.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Walt Disney Company has agreed to buy most of 21st Century Fox’s assets in a deal worth $52.4 billion, but things got complicated last week when Comcast made a rival offer that valued the business at $65 billion.

headline.main: With Two Suitors for Fox, the Murdochs Consider Next Steps
headline.print_headline: Fox’s Suitors Prepare to Duel. Either Way, Murdoch Wins.

docs.abstract: Antitrust experts say the enforcement of laws governing mergers should be updated to reflect major changes to the economy over the past 40 years.

docs.lead_paragraph: The last time there was an antitrust ruling as important as the one handed down Tuesday by Judge Richard J. Leon, cellphones didn’t exist. There was no such thing as the internet. Personal computers were years away from mass adoption.

docs.abstract: Only recently has the Federal Reserve tried to communicate directly and transparently to the public. Its new chairman is pushing ahead on that frontier.
docs.snippet: Only recently has the Federal Reserve tried to communicate directly and transparently to the public. Its new chairman is pushing ahead on that frontier.
docs.lead_paragraph: Federal Reserve chiefs were long known for saying little, and making what they did say as opaque as possible. It’s been barely seven years since central bankers began to hold news conferences after policy meetings — and even then, only on alternate occasions.

headline.main: Was This a Fed Chief Talking? How Powell Sounded Different
